Appendix F: World Model Training Details

The world model is trained online using a combination of reconstruction loss (if generative) and KL regularization. The standard approach (Hafner et al., 2023) uses a recurrent state‑space model (RSSM):

· Deterministic recurrent state: h_t = f(h_{t-1}, z_{t-1}, a_{t-1})
· Stochastic latent: z_t \sim p_\psi(z_t \mid h_t)
· Observation decoder: o_t \sim p_\psi(o_t \mid h_t, z_t)
· Reward decoder: r_t \sim p_\psi(r_t \mid h_t, z_t)

Training minimizes the ELBO:

\mathcal{L} = \sum_{t=1}^T \left( -\log p_\psi(o_t \mid h_t, z_t) - \log p_\psi(r_t \mid h_t, z_t) + \beta_{\mathrm{KL}} D_{\mathrm{KL}}\big( q_\phi(z_t \mid o_t, h_t) \,\|\, p_\psi(z_t \mid h_t) \big) \right).
\]  

The term \beta_{\mathrm{KL}} balances the reconstruction and regularization.

For the JEPA‑style non‑generative model, we replace the reconstruction loss with a contrastive loss that predicts embeddings of future observations, thereby avoiding pixel‑level reconstruction and saving computation.

